modules.description: Handles character substitutions for specific languages using predefined mappings. Works with tuples of strings representing character replacements. Used to customize slug generation for different language character sets.

Works with lists of character replacement rules to build custom mappings for transforming strings into URL-safe slugs. Provides `mk_charmap` to construct a charmap from replacement lists and `base` to access the default charmap. Used to customize character substitutions during slugification, such as handling locale-specific characters or defining custom replacements.

Transforms strings into URL-safe slugs by replacing non-alphanumeric characters and applying customizable character mappings. Works with UTF-8 strings and supports configurable separators, case handling, and language-specific substitutions. Used to generate clean, SEO-friendly URLs from arbitrary text inputs.
